tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE network_configuration_changes (
  change_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  change_date TIMESTAMP,
  user_id INT,
  change_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE network_configuration_changes (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  change_type VARCHAR,
  configuration_details TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR,
  email VARCHAR,
  role VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE audit_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  user_id INT,
  action VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE audit_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    action VARCHAR(50),
    details TEXT,
    user_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE audit_logs (
    log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT REFERENCES users(user_id),
    action VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    log_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    details JSON
);
